  final String english_pr =
      "For a long time, the name of Bholad's Surapura Dada is resonating not only in Gujarat but in the whole of India. People go to every corner of the world and finally come to the feet of Bholad Surapura Dada. And let me tell you that Surapura Dada has also relieved the sorrows of many people. \n\n Friends, nowadays people are considering superstition as faith. In such a situation, the question arises, whether Palia Veer Tejaji and Veer Rajaji Surapura, who are worshipped as Khambi, would still be present today or is it just people's faith. Friends, to know the importance of this place, do read till the end. \n\n The pillars of Veer Tejaji Dada and Veer Rajaji Dada, who sacrificed their lives to protect a Charan's daughter about 900 years ago, are in Surapura Dham. People from every corner of the state come to visit the temple of Surapura Dada without any discrimination of caste. And here Dada fulfills everyone's wishes. Friends, today in every village, the pillars of Palia stone standing in front of Suryanarayan Dev are known as Surapura. \n\n Friends, both the life and death of these brave warriors are inspiring. They, without caring for their children and family, ended the worldly attachments in a moment to protect cows, Brahmins, women and religion and offered their heads at the feet of Mahadev. Even today, after 900 years, they are worshipped for their great deeds. \n\n The pillar of the brave warrior that we are talking about today is currently located in Bholad village near Rothar on Pipli Vataman Road on Dhingi land. Suryanarayan temple is situated at a place called Pithdia Bhal, 5 kms from Bholad, leaving Rajasthan. And in front of it is Veer Raja Ji and Veer Teja Ji Dada Ki Khambhi. \n\n If we introduce Veer Raja Ji and Teja Ji, they were sons of Vikram Singh and Ganga Maa and Chauhan Rajputs of Kshatriya clan. When robbers attacked Charan's daughter, Charan came to save the honor of the girl and killed 17 robbers. But then he was attacked from behind. \n\n Friends, it is said that when a Kshatriya goes to the battlefield to protect religion, then Maa Bhavani resides in him. And he sacrificed his life at the young age of just 27 years and became immortal. Then many years passed and many Chauhan Rajputs from outside started coming to visit Dada Ki Khambhi. But when Dada showed miracles to Chauhan of Bholad, it was decided to establish a suitable place for him. \n\n It was established on Hanuman Jayanti on Vikram Samvat 2072 Chaitra Sud Purnima Tithi (22/04/2016 - Friday) at Bholad Nani Borun Road. Dada has also shown his presence in today's era by giving miracle of his presence. That is why people of all castes from every corner of the world come here with faith to visit. And people are doing public service by donating selflessly and feeding people. \n\n It seems as if the duty of service remained incomplete while alive, but Dada is today taking the society on the right path. And helping in trouble. Dada Danbha (Balwant Singh Chauhan) is working in the service of the temple. \n\n Let us also tell you that here the service of Food is given 24 hours. And Dada himself is managing it without any paper, pen or book. The sons and daughters of the society also stand in the service of Dada. If we talk about the valour, courage and sacrifice of Palia Dev standing at the entrance of the village then even books will fall short.";

  final String hindi_pr =
